---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

const description = "How to negotiate hospital bills and reduce medical debt by 20-60%. Financial assistance programs, cash-pay discounts, and payment plans.";
---

<Base title="Negotiate Hospital Bills — CreditCookbook" description="{description}" posterTitle="NEGOTIATE" posterLabel="// 05 — reduce your bill">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-label">// content</span>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom: 24px;">How to negotiate hospital bills</h2>
      <p>Most people don't know that hospital chargemaster prices are negotiable. Hospitals expect insurance to negotiate down, so the sticker price is inflated 3-10x the actual cost. When you pay cash, you can negotiate the same discounts — or better.</p>

<h3 style="margin-top: 40px;">The 4-step negotiation process</h3>
<ol style="margin-left: 24px; line-height: 2.5; margin-bottom: 32px;">
  <li><strong>Request an itemized bill.</strong> You have a right to this. Review every charge — up to 80% of hospital bills contain errors.</li>
  <li><strong>Ask for the cash-pay rate.</strong> Hospitals have a "chargemaster" price and a "cash-pay" price. The cash price is typically 40-60% lower.</li>
  <li><strong>Apply for financial assistance (charity care).</strong> Nonprofit hospitals are required by law to offer financial assistance. Income thresholds vary but many cover 200-400% of federal poverty level.</li>
  <li><strong>Set up an interest-free payment plan.</strong> If you can't pay in full, hospitals will accept monthly payments — often with no interest and no collection threat as long as you're paying.</li>
</ol>

<h3 style="margin-bottom: 16px;">Negotiation script</h3>
<div class="mono-block" style="margin-bottom: 32px;">
"Hi, I'm calling about my bill for [AMOUNT] from
[DATE OF SERVICE]. I'd like to discuss payment options.

I'm unable to pay the full amount, but I'd like to
work out a reduced rate. I understand there's a cash-pay
discount — can you tell me what that would be for my
bill?

I'd also like to apply for your financial assistance
program. Can you send me the application?"

[IF THEY OFFER A DISCOUNT]
"Thank you. I can pay [OFFERED AMOUNT] in full today
if we can settle this and close the account."

[IF THEY CAN'T REDUCE]
"I understand. Can we set up a payment plan of
[$X/MONTH] so I can pay this off without it going
to collections?"
</div>

<div class="card">
  <h4 style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Key facts</h4>
  <ul style="margin-left: 24px; line-height: 2;">
    <li>80% of hospital bills contain errors — always request itemization</li>
    <li>Cash-pay rates are typically 40-60% below chargemaster</li>
    <li>Nonprofit hospitals must offer charity care (IRC 501(r) requirement)</li>
    <li>Payment plans are interest-free at most nonprofit hospitals</li>
    <li>Never ignore a bill — unpaid bills go to collections after 90-180 days</li>
  </ul>
</div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
